Chelsea’s squad to face Real Madrid in tonight’s Champions League first-leg tie has been revealed. According to Football London, Chelsea manager, Thomas Tuchel, has named a 23-man squad to face Real Madrid at Stamford Bridge. Chelsea head to the game after losing 4-1 to Brentford in the Premier League last weekend. Real Madrid, meanwhile, won 2-1 against Celta Vigo in a LaLiga tie. Below is Chelsea’s full squad against Real Madrid: Goalkeepers: Edouard Mendy, Kepa Arrizabalaga, Marcus Bettinelli Defenders: Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Thiago Silva, Antonio Rudiger, Andreas Christensen, Malang Sarr, Trevoh Chalobah, Marcos Alonso, Kenedy Midfielders: N’Golo Kante, Jorginho, Mateo Kovacic, Ruben Loftus-Cheek, Saul Niguez, Ross Barkley, Mason Mount, Christian Pulisic Forwards: Timo Werner, Romelu Lukaku, Kai Havertz The kick-off time for the match is 8 pm.